verbose_text: We also conducted analyses of quartiles of fructosamine, glycated albumin, and 1,5-AG stratified by baseline categories of fasting glucose (< 100 mg/dL and 100-125 mg/dL) or A1C (< 5.7 and 5.7-6.4%) to see if any associations of alternative markers of glycemia with incident diabetes persisted among persons with glucose or A1C levels in the normal or prediabetic ranges.
